jalse.attributes

Class AttributeSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<java.lang.Object>
        • jalse.attributes.AttributeSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.Object>, java.util.Set<java.lang.Object>

    public class AttributeSet
extends java.util.AbstractSet<java.lang.Object>
    An AttributeSet is a thread-safe Set implementation for AttributeType values. An AttributeSet follows the same pattern defined in AttributeContainer but offers a collections based implementation (so it may be used more generically). This set considers types to be unique on name only.

    AttributeSet can take a delegate AttributeContainer to supply to AttributeEvent. Attribute updates will trigger these events using AttributeListener.
    Author:
    Elliot Ford
